<subSubSection id="68DEC5F83D42FFA5FF4DFA26FB7BF99F" box="[199,1168,1519,1546]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="207B96733D42FFA5FF4DFA26FB7BF99F" blockId="49.[151,1437,1447,2014]" box="[199,1168,1519,1546]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis id="12B04A613D42FFA5FF4DFA26FEA3F99F" bold="true" box="[199,328,1519,1545]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Etymology</emphasis>
. The specific epithet is referring to the ventral projection of the chelicerae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="68DEC5F83D42FFA5FF4DF9DAFD54F9EE" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="207B96733D42FFA5FF4DF9DAFD54F9EE" blockId="49.[151,1437,1447,2014]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis id="12B04A613D42FFA5FF4DF9DAFEA9F9BB" bold="true" box="[199,322,1555,1581]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males 
<taxonomicName id="E7C4EDF03D42FFA5FE1EF9DDFDAEF9BB" authority="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Villarreal &amp; Oliveira, 2021" authorityName="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Villarreal &amp; Oliveira" authorityYear="2021" box="[404,581,1555,1581]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Patrera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dentata" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="12B04A613D42FFA5FE1EF9DDFDAEF9BB" box="[404,581,1555,1581]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Patrera dentata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="12B04A613D42FFA5FDC1F9DAFD61F9BB" bold="true" box="[587,650,1555,1581]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="0983F71A3D42FFA5FDC1F9DAFD61F9BB" box="[587,650,1555,1581]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
can be distinguished from those of the remaining species of the genus by the slender, elongated ventral tegular apophysis closely related to the embolus and by the presence of a second triangular, small tegular projection (
<figureCitation id="B8FF8AF63D42FFA5FDA0F992FD78F9EE" box="[554,659,1627,1656]" captionStart="FIGURE 26" captionStartId="50.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[170,1405,181,1914]" captionTargetId="figure-27@50.[164,1424,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="50" captionText="FIGURE 26A–D. Patrera dentata n. sp. Male (ICN-Ar-10636):A habitus, dorsal view; B chelicerae, dorsal view; C chelicerae, ventral view; D left palp, retroventral view; E palp, ventral view; F palp, retrolateral view. Abbreviations: Cavp, cheliceral anteroventral projection; VTP, ventral tegular process. Scale bars: A: 2mm; B–C: 1mm; D: 0.5mm; E–F: 0.2mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468441" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4468441/files/figure.png" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Fig. 26D</figureCitation>
̅F).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="68DEC5F83D42FFA0FF4DF9B6FE49FEF3" lastPageId="52" lastPageNumber="53" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" type="description">
<paragraph id="207B96733D42FFA0FF4DF9B6FB2EFED4" blockId="49.[151,1437,1447,2014]" lastBlockId="52.[151,1437,150,393]" lastPageId="52" lastPageNumber="53" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis id="12B04A613D42FFA5FF4DF9B6FEB2F90F" bold="true" box="[199,345,1663,1689]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="12B04A613D42FFA5FED4F9B6FE73F90F" box="[350,408,1663,1689]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Male</emphasis>
(
<typeStatus id="FF7F28D13D42FFA5FE2FF9B6FDF9F90F" box="[421,530,1663,1689]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Holotype</typeStatus>
, ICN-Ar-10636). Carapace from cephalic zone to thoracic groove pale brown, lateral and posterior margin yellow (
<figureCitation id="B8FF8AF63D42FFA5FD9EF96AFD97F928" box="[532,636,1699,1726]" captionStart="FIGURE 26" captionStartId="50.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[170,1405,181,1914]" captionTargetId="figure-27@50.[164,1424,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="50" captionText="FIGURE 26A–D. Patrera dentata n. sp. Male (ICN-Ar-10636):A habitus, dorsal view; B chelicerae, dorsal view; C chelicerae, ventral view; D left palp, retroventral view; E palp, ventral view; F palp, retrolateral view. Abbreviations: Cavp, cheliceral anteroventral projection; VTP, ventral tegular process. Scale bars: A: 2mm; B–C: 1mm; D: 0.5mm; E–F: 0.2mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468441" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4468441/files/figure.png" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Fig. 26A</figureCitation>
). Chelicerae red brownish (
<figureCitation id="B8FF8AF63D42FFA5FC3BF96AFBF1F928" box="[945,1050,1699,1726]" captionStart="FIGURE 26" captionStartId="50.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[170,1405,181,1914]" captionTargetId="figure-27@50.[164,1424,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="50" captionText="FIGURE 26A–D. Patrera dentata n. sp. Male (ICN-Ar-10636):A habitus, dorsal view; B chelicerae, dorsal view; C chelicerae, ventral view; D left palp, retroventral view; E palp, ventral view; F palp, retrolateral view. Abbreviations: Cavp, cheliceral anteroventral projection; VTP, ventral tegular process. Scale bars: A: 2mm; B–C: 1mm; D: 0.5mm; E–F: 0.2mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468441" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4468441/files/figure.png" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Fig. 26A</figureCitation>
). Labium and endites brown. Sternum yellow. Legs yellow. Abdomen gray covered of black setae; ventrally light gray. Spinnerets yellow (
<figureCitation id="B8FF8AF63D42FFA5FAA2F90EFA7BF974" box="[1320,1424,1735,1762]" captionStart="FIGURE 26" captionStartId="50.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[170,1405,181,1914]" captionTargetId="figure-27@50.[164,1424,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="50" captionText="FIGURE 26A–D. Patrera dentata n. sp. Male (ICN-Ar-10636):A habitus, dorsal view; B chelicerae, dorsal view; C chelicerae, ventral view; D left palp, retroventral view; E palp, ventral view; F palp, retrolateral view. Abbreviations: Cavp, cheliceral anteroventral projection; VTP, ventral tegular process. Scale bars: A: 2mm; B–C: 1mm; D: 0.5mm; E–F: 0.2mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468441" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4468441/files/figure.png" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Fig. 26A</figureCitation>
). Total length 6.53, carapace length 2.81, width 2.17, high 0.95. Clypeus height 0.13. Eye diameters and interdistances:AME 0.09, ALE 0.19, PME 0.18, PLE 0.21; AME–AME 0.21, AME–ALE 0.37, PME–PME 0.5, PME–PLE 0.47, ALE–PLE 0.39. Chelicerae 1.56 long, three promarginal teeth, the second largest, four retromarginal teeth; Cavp large (
<figureCitation id="B8FF8AF63D42FFA5FEAAF89EFE63F8E7" box="[288,392,1879,1905]" captionStart="FIGURE 28" captionStartId="53.[151,250,1882,1906]" captionTargetBox="[152,1431,237,1858]" captionTargetId="figure-56@53.[151,1436,237,1858]" captionTargetPageId="53" captionText="FIGURE 28A–G Patrera kuryi n. sp. Male (IBSP 213425): A habitus, dorsal view; C left palp, retroventral view; D palp, ventral view; E palp, retrolateral view. Female (IBSP 213429): B habitus, dorsal view; F epigynum, ventral view; G epigynum, dorsal view. Abbreviations: FD, fertilization ducts; VTP, ventral tegular process. Scale bars: A–B: 2.16mm; C–E: 0.6mm; F–G: 0.25mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468445" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4468445/files/figure.png" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Fig. 28C</figureCitation>
